<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="110" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,725]" box="[189,812,158,184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Phenology:—Flowering &amp; fruiting: August–November.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,725]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
Ecology:—Growing on moss covered wet tree trunks in evergreen forests, along with 
<taxonomicName authority="Ratheesh, Sujanapal &amp; Meera (2011: 154)" authorityName="Ratheesh, Sujanapal &amp; Meera" authorityPageNumber="154" authorityYear="2011" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="veerapazhasii">
<emphasis box="[1176,1452,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Impatiens veerapazhasii</emphasis>
Ratheesh, Sujanapal &amp; Meera (2011: 154)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lindl. (1830: 16)" authorityName="Lindl." authorityPageNumber="16" authorityYear="1830" box="[612,1009,230,257]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Oberonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bicornis">
<emphasis box="[612,815,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Oberonia bicornis</emphasis>
Lindl. (1830: 16)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ratheesh, Manudev &amp; Sujanapal (2010: 713)" authorityName="Ratheesh, Manudev &amp; Sujanapal" authorityPageNumber="713" authorityYear="2010" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Oberonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="swaminathanii">
<emphasis box="[1060,1336,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Oberonia swaminathanii</emphasis>
Ratheesh, Manudev &amp; Sujanapal (2010: 713)
</taxonomicName>
, at an elevation of 
<quantity box="[741,829,266,293]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.31" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" unit="m" value="1310.0">1310 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="110" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,725]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
Conservation Status:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saravanan &amp; Kaliamoorthy" authorityYear="2022" box="[454,690,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keralensis">
<emphasis box="[454,690,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Impatiens keralensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[991,1039,303,329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">type</typeStatus>
locality with about 10–12 mature individuals. The population is well conserved within the boundaries of protected forest areas. However, considering the lesser number of individuals in a single population size distributed in an area of hardly 
<quantity box="[1129,1209,374,400]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" unit="km" value="0.3">0.3 km</quantity>
, the species described here is assessed as Critically Endangered (CE) by applying the criterion d (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Committee" box="[976,1114,410,436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" refId="ref4176" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee (2019) Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List categories and Criteria. Version 14. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 10 November 2020)" type="book" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1290,446,473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,725]" box="[189,1290,446,473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
Etymology:—The species is named after the 
<collectingRegion box="[695,831,446,473]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Kerala state</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[842,902,446,472]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">India</collectingCountry>
, where the 
<typeStatus box="[1030,1078,447,473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">type</typeStatus>
locality is present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="110" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,725]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
Notes:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saravanan &amp; Kaliamoorthy" authorityYear="2022" box="[290,526,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keralensis">
<emphasis box="[290,526,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Impatiens keralensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also allied to 
<taxonomicName authority="C. E. C. Fisch. (1935: 157)" authorityName="C. E. C. Fisch." authorityPageNumber="157" authorityYear="1935" box="[726,1198,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dendricola">
<emphasis box="[726,874,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. dendricola</emphasis>
C. E. C. Fisch. (1935:157)
</taxonomicName>
, in having a tuberous scapigerous epiphytic habit, radical leaves, flowers in racemose scapes, white flowers and presence of spur, but differs in the size and shape of the bract (slightly falcate in 
<emphasis box="[751,1017,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saravanan &amp; Kaliamoorthy" authorityYear="2022" box="[751,985,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keralensis">Impatiens keralensis</taxonomicName>
vs
</emphasis>
ovate in 
<taxonomicName box="[1130,1277,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dendricola">
<emphasis box="[1130,1277,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. dendricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), lateral sepals (obliquely oblong in 
<emphasis box="[378,643,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saravanan &amp; Kaliamoorthy" authorityYear="2022" box="[378,611,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keralensis">Impatiens keralensis</taxonomicName>
vs
</emphasis>
asymmetrically ovate in 
<taxonomicName box="[934,1080,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dendricola">
<emphasis box="[934,1080,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. dendricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), dorsal petal (obtuse at apex in 
<emphasis box="[136,401,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saravanan &amp; Kaliamoorthy" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,369,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keralensis">Impatiens keralensis</taxonomicName>
vs
</emphasis>
retuse at apex in 
<taxonomicName box="[607,753,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dendricola">
<emphasis box="[607,753,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. dendricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), wing petals (papillose at the base of mid-lobe in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saravanan &amp; Kaliamoorthy" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keralensis">Impatiens keralensis</taxonomicName>
vs
</emphasis>
hairs at the base in 
<taxonomicName box="[504,649,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dendricola">
<emphasis box="[504,649,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. dendricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), spur (straight in 
<emphasis box="[858,1119,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saravanan &amp; Kaliamoorthy" authorityYear="2022" box="[858,1089,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keralensis">Impatiens keralensis</taxonomicName>
vs
</emphasis>
clavate in 
<taxonomicName box="[1242,1387,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dendricola">
<emphasis box="[1242,1387,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. dendricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and dorsal auricle (absent in 
<emphasis box="[411,672,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saravanan &amp; Kaliamoorthy" authorityYear="2022" box="[411,643,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="keralensis">Impatiens keralensis</taxonomicName>
vs
</emphasis>
present in 
<taxonomicName box="[796,941,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dendricola">
<emphasis box="[796,941,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. dendricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
